  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 561720 (Janitorial Services) federal contract obligations in FY2026 to date total $1.1B across 3,897 awards with an average award size of $272K. Obligations are down 40.7% year over year, and FY2026 to date obligations are lower than FY25 obligations of $1.8B. The Department of Defense accounts for the single largest share of FY2026 to date spending at $639M, followed by the Department of Veterans Affairs at $83.7M and the General Services Administration at $56M. Top vendor obligations in FY2026 to date include GLOBAL CONNECTIONS TO EMPLOYMENT, INC. at $43.3M, FEDCAP REHABILITATION SERVICES, INC at $39.1M, and TEYA SUPPORT SERVICES LLC at $33M. The FY series shows fiscal-year obligations moving from $1.6B (FY21) and $1.6B (FY22) to $1.7B (FY23), $1.7B (FY24), $1.8B (FY25), and $1.1B (FY26). These figures reflect fiscal-year-to-date totals and highlight a contraction in obligations in the current fiscal year compared with the prior full fiscal year.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has federal spending on NAICS 561720 changed over recent fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations climbed from $1.6B in FY21 and $1.6B in FY22 to $1.7B in FY23 and $1.7B in FY24 before peaking at $1.8B in FY25 and then falling to $1.1B in FY26. Obligations are down 40.7% year over year, indicating a notable decline in the current fiscal-year-to-date total compared with the prior year."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate NAICS 561720 obligations in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense dominates FY2026 to date obligations with $639M, well ahead of the Department of Veterans Affairs at $83.7M and the General Services Administration at $56M. Leading vendors by obligations in FY2026 to date include GLOBAL CONNECTIONS TO EMPLOYMENT, INC. at $43.3M, FEDCAP REHABILITATION SERVICES, INC at $39.1M, and TEYA SUPPORT SERVICES LLC at $33M."
